    <body>
        <head type="sub"><num xml:lang="en">1</num>. <term xml:lang="ta">ēmam eṉṉum peyar</term></head>
        <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="Tiv11.1">
          <l>cēmaṅ kāva liṉpa miravupoṉ</l>
          <l>ēmāppu mayakka mēma mākum.</l>
        </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
          <l>Well-being, protection, delight, the night,<note place="foot">This seems to reflect the possibility that <foreign xml:lang="ta">ēmam</foreign> is a variant spelling for <foreign xml:lang="ta">yāmam</foreign>.</note> wealth,<note place="foot">The semantic field for Sanskrit <foreign xml:lang="sa">kṣema</foreign> suggests that <foreign xml:lang="ta">poṉ</foreign> means <q>wealth</q> here, rather than the more literal <q>gold.</q> However, it may also reflect the possibility of <foreign xml:lang="ta">ēmam</foreign> being derived from Sanskrit <foreign xml:lang="sa">hēman</foreign>.</note></l>
          <l>security, stupor — are <foreign xml:lang="ta-Latn">ēmam</foreign>.</l>
        </lg>
        </div>

        <head type="sub"><num xml:lang="en">2273</num>. <term xml:lang="ta">toyyil eṉṉum peyar</term></head>
        <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="Tiv11.372">
          <l>uḻavu nīri leḻuvatōr putalum</l>
          <l>kuḻaivu makiḻcciyu maḻaku meṉṟivai</l>
          <l>tuyaruṅ kūṟun toyyiṟ kiḷavi.<anchor xml:id="Tiv2273-note1"/></l>
          <trailer>(372)</trailer>
        </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
            <l>The word <foreign xml:lang="ta-Latn">toyyil</foreign> refers to:</l>
            <l rend="indent">ploughing, water spinach (i.e. a shrub growing in water),</l>
            <l rend="indent">these — tenderness, delight, &amp; beauty —,</l>
            <l rend="indent">and grief.</l>
        </lg>
        </div>

        <head type="sub"><num xml:lang="en">2274</num>. <term xml:lang="ta">arākam eṉṉum peyar</term></head>
        <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="Tiv11.373">
          <l>kītamu niṟamuñ cenniṟak keḻuvu</l>
          <l>mācaiyu muṭukiyalu marāka meṉappaṭum.<anchor xml:id="Tiv2274-note1"/></l>
          <trailer>(373)</trailer>
        </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
            <l><foreign xml:lang="ta-Latn">Arākam</foreign> is said to be:</l>
            <l rend="indent">a song, a colour, having a red colour,</l>
            <l rend="indent">desire, or a <foreign>muṭukiyal</foreign> verse.</l>
        </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
