<standOff corresp="#Tiv11.372" type="notes1">
<note xml:lang="en" target="#Tiv2273-note1">The critical edition reads <foreign xml:lang="ta">uḻavunīril</foreign> together, understanding something like <q>in ploughing water</q>. This perhaps works better with the variant reading <foreign xml:lang="ta">uḻavunilattil</foreign>, <q>in ploughed land</q>. However, as one variant reading at the end of line 2 shows (<foreign xml:lang="ta-Latn">eṉa vaintun</foreign>), the first two lines have been interpreted as containing 5 items. Moreover, <foreign xml:lang="ta-Latn">toyyal</foreign> is given as a synonym for <foreign xml:lang="ta-Latn">uḻavu</foreign> in <title xml:lang="ta">Cūṭāmaṇi</title> <ref target="https://archive.org/details/dli.jZY9lup2kZl6TuXGlZQdjZp7kZUy.TVA_BOK_0002448/page/411/mode/1up">5.61</ref>. The variant reading of <foreign xml:lang="ta-Latn">toyyal</foreign> for <foreign xml:lang="ta-Latn">toyyil</foreign> is not recorded in the critical edition, but it is found in <abbr corresp="#BnF239"/>.</note>
</standOff>
